.TH "dwc2_hcd_disconnect" 9 "dwc2_hcd_disconnect" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
dwc2_hcd_disconnect \- Handles disconnect of the HCD
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" dwc2_hcd_disconnect
.BI "(struct dwc2_hsotg *hsotg "  ","
.BI "bool force "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "hsotg" 12
Pointer to struct dwc2_hsotg
.IP "force" 12
If true, we won't try to reconnect even if we see device connected.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Must be called with interrupt disabled and spinlock held
